I used &quot;spar varnish&quot;. Its a varnish designed for outside used, and is very
hard. It cannot be buffed out to a shine, the final coat must be sprayed. I
brushed about 8 coats on it, sanding between every coat and sprayed the last
two coats. I would have had a better finish if I had a spray booth to work
with. It turned out real well. but I can see the mistakes!!
See it at:  http://sacketttt.tripod.com/1950_F-1p3.htm
The kid at Menards tried to sell me Thompson's deck stuff, I was trying to
tell him I needed it to shine.

